Beef Bourguignon, also known as Beef Burgundy, is a classic French dish that originated in the Burgundy region of France. It is a hearty and flavourful stew made with tender chunks of beef, red wine, and vegetables. The dish is slow-cooked to perfection, resulting in a rich and delicious meal that is perfect for the whole family. The dish has a long history, dating back to the 19th century, and has become a beloved comfort food for foodies around the world. Tried, tested, and true â€“ this recipe by the number one-selling multi-cooker Instant Pot is a real crowd-pleaser! 